docs.abstract: Republicans had hope after 2022 that the nation’s residential redoubts were coming back to the G.O.P. But aside from New York, the suburbs on Tuesday swung back to the Democrats.
docs.snippet: Republicans had hope after 2022 that the nation’s residential redoubts were coming back to the G.O.P. But aside from New York, the suburbs on Tuesday swung back to the Democrats.
docs.lead_paragraph: From Northern Virginia to Northern Kentucky, the American suburbs rejected Republican candidates on Tuesday, sending a message that leafy residential communities where elections were once won and lost increasingly side with the Democratic Party — especially on abortion rights.

headline.main: Suburbs Were Democratic Turf on Tuesday. What About in 2024?
headline.print_headline: Suburbs Went Democratic  On Tuesday. How About ’24?

headline.main: In New Hampshire, a Democratic Congressman Debates Ramaswamy
headline.print_headline: Republican Long Shot Tries to Use Debate to Revive His Campaign

docs.abstract: Representative Summer Lee of Pennsylvania, who joined calls for a cease-fire, has become one of several progressive lawmakers facing new pressure from primary challengers.
docs.snippet: Representative Summer Lee of Pennsylvania, who joined calls for a cease-fire, has become one of several progressive lawmakers facing new pressure from primary challengers.
docs.lead_paragraph: As Congregation Beth Shalom in Pittsburgh observed a special evening of prayer on Oct. 22 for the Israeli captives in Gaza, Representative Summer Lee, the progressive Democrat whose district includes the synagogue, paid her respects. She was late to arrive and could not stay long, but the rabbi, Seth Adelson, called her chief of staff the next day to offer his thanks.

headline.main: Primary Battles Brew Over Progressive Democrats’ Stances on Israel
headline.print_headline: Progressive Democrats Face Primary Challenges Over a Lack of Support for Israel

docs.abstract: After Donald J. Trump bound himself tightly to the Israeli right, and President Biden approached the divided nation gingerly, a warm presidential embrace has eased years of tension.
docs.snippet: After Donald J. Trump bound himself tightly to the Israeli right, and President Biden approached the divided nation gingerly, a warm presidential embrace has eased years of tension.
docs.lead_paragraph: Not long ago, Donald J. Trump occupied enormous psychological space in Israel and among American Jews: His face draped skyscrapers alongside Benjamin Netanyahu’s during Israeli elections, and his politics drove a wedge between the Democratic Party and the Jews who have long called it their political home.

headline.main: Israeli Billboards Thanking the U.S. Have a New Face on Them: Biden’s

docs.abstract: This week’s electoral victories for abortion rights offer lessons ahead of next November.
docs.snippet: This week’s electoral victories for abortion rights offer lessons ahead of next November.
docs.lead_paragraph: With two election cycles after the decision in Dobbs v. Jackson Women’s Health Organization under our belts, it cannot be denied: Abortion rights are the dominant issue in American politics. And when supporters of abortion rights — a clear majority of Americans — see a connection between their votes and protecting what was once guaranteed by Roe v. Wade, they are more likely to vote.

headline.main: American Elections Are About Abortion Now
headline.print_headline: American Elections Are Now About Abortion
